cs.FL, cs.LO, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.PL 

This paper deals with the decidability of functionality of visibly pushdown transducers, which is a topic related to formal languages and automata theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory). The paper also uses techniques of word combinatorics, which is a subfield of discrete mathematics, making cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) another likely category. The use of pumping argument and the complexity analysis of equivalence also suggest that the paper could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.PL (Programming Languages). Finally, the paper deals with the theoretical aspects of computation, which could make it relevant to cs.IT (Information Theory).
